org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit

Class CommitOperations

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.CommitOperations

  • public class CommitOperations
extends Object
    The implementation of the various actions a committer needs. This doesn't implement the protocol/binding to a specific execution engine, just the operations needed to to build one. When invoking FS operations, it assumes that the underlying FS is handling retries and exception translation: it does not attempt to duplicate that work.

      static class  CommitOperations.MaybeIOE
      A holder for a possible IOException; the call CommitOperations.MaybeIOE.maybeRethrow() will throw any exception passed into the constructor, and be a no-op if none was.
